        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 5:00PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 500 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of El Porvenir, or 8 miles west of Las Vegas, moving
east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Montezuma, San Geronimo, San Pablo, Mineral Hill and Ojitos Frios.

This includes the following highways...
State Road 283 between Mile Markers 4 and 12.
State Road 65 between Mile Markers 2 and 9.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rains from severe thunderstorms can produce sudden and
dangerous flows in arroyos, ditches and over low water crossings. Do
not attempt to drive through areas where water covers the roadway.</instruction>
